Business Brief -- L.M. Ericsson AB:
   Pact Is Reached to Build
   Phone System in Portugal
Telecel is a telecommunications joint venture of Pacific
Telesis Group and several Portuguese companies. In October,
it obtained the license to operate the private digital
cellular system in Portugal.
   Ericsson said the Portuguese contract strengthens its
position in the European cellular market. Of 14 countries
that have chosen an equipment supplier, 11 have chosen
Ericsson. The company also said it has a 40% world share in
cellular mobile systems, or 5.4 million of the world's 13.2
million cellular subscribers as of August.